cc.alcina.framework.common.client.logic.reflection
Annotation Type Association

@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Documented
public @interface Association

Optional Element Summary
 java.lang.Class implementationClass
          The type name of the implementation class (component type for a collection, implementation type for an interface) of this end of this association - e.g.
 java.lang.String propertyName
          The property name of the other end of this association - e.g.
 boolean silentUpdates
          Do not update the other end of this association when consuming a DomainTransformEvent - this is useful for performance reasons (parent-child associations with 1000s of kids spring to mind)
 

propertyName

public abstract java.lang.String propertyName
The property name of the other end of this association - e.g. for:
Bookstore Book.getBookstore() and
Set<Book> Bookstore.getBooks()
the getBookstore method would have association with propertyName "books"

Default:
""

implementationClass

public abstract java.lang.Class implementationClass
The type name of the implementation class (component type for a collection, implementation type for an interface) of this end of this association - e.g. for:
Bookstore Book.getBookstore() and
Set<Book> Bookstore.getBooks()
the getBookstore() method would have association with implementationClass "Bookstore" and the getBookss() method would have association with implementationClass "Book"

Default:
void.class

silentUpdates

public abstract boolean silentUpdates
Do not update the other end of this association when consuming a DomainTransformEvent - this is useful for performance reasons (parent-child associations with 1000s of kids spring to mind)

Default:
false
